
'''* Book: Occupy Consciousness: Essays on the Global Insurrection. Evolver, 2012.'''

URL = http://www.realitysandwich.com/occupy_consciousness_book


=Description=

Daniel Pinchbeck:

"The Evolver Social Movement just released a free e-book anthology that
brings together a variety of perspectives on Occupy, offering a
multi-dimensional approach to the ongoing insurrection. At a time when
the initial energy around Occupy has flagged in some areas, we believe
this anthology is a powerful tool as it explores not just the politics
but also the subtler dimensions of the movement, which is more about
process than protest.

With essays by Doug Rushkoff, David Graeber, Starhawk, Russell Brand,
and many more, Occupy Consciousness: Essays on the Global Insurrection
takes a visionary approach to the culture, strategies, mythology, and
possible future of Occupy – or whatever will develop from it. Occupy
Consciousness looks at Occupy, not just as a protest movement, but as
a harbinger of a new way of being – a new mode of cooperation and
collaboration."


